Scala Program to Print Numbers from 1 to 100
using for loop
object PrintNumbers {
def main(args: Array[String]): Unit = {

for(i &lt;- 1 to 100) {
println(i)
}

}
}

Steps to Run in Ubuntu
1. Create file
nano PrintNumbers.scala

2. Paste the code and save
3. Compile
scalac PrintNumbers.scala

4. Run
scala PrintNumbers
